Slovakia’s Sulik Opposes Increase in Size of EFSF, Welt Reports

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-08-26T16:39:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/slovakia-s-sulik-opposes-increase-in-size-of-efsf-welt-reports.html
Richard Sulik, chairman of Freedom
and Solidarity, one of Slovakia’s four ruling parties, said he
opposes any increase in the size of the European Financial
Stability Facility,  Welt newspaper  reported in a preview of an
interview that will be published tomorrow.  “We’re not saving the Greeks, but the profits of the
German and French banks,” Sulik said, according to Welt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  